description.narrative: 1.2. By 2021, mothers and new-borns in selected districts have access to high impact interventions before, during pregnancy and after delivery for preventing preventable maternal and new-borns deaths, which contributes to Adolescent Health And Nutrition, Immunization, Maternal And Newborn Health, Maternal And Newborn Health (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: 1. By 2021, children (including newborns and adolescents) and pregnant women benefit from improved and equitable high-impact maternal, neonatal, child and adolescent health interventions and behaviors.

description.narrative: Public Health guidelines and protocols to support continuity of maternal newborn health services were developed and distributed; support provided to strengthen commodity security of essential maternal newborn health drugs and supplies and infection prevention equipment. All districts provide Basic Emergency Obstetric and New-born Care (BEmONC) 24 hours a day and the country has continued to use the scorecard on Reproductive, Maternal, Newborn and Child Health to monitor progress and take corrective action at all levels of the health system. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:30/06/2020
